==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Economist
<hw>E*con"o*mist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧conomiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
economizes, or manages domestic or other concerns with frugality; one
who expends money, time, or labor, judiciously, and without waste.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Economists</xex> even to parsimony.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who is conversant with political economy; an
expert in the field of economics.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Economization</ent>⟦br⟧
